This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with clinical text summarization using computational linguistics techniques. It also involves the use of semantic information and knowledge base, which are common in natural language processing research. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper utilizes machine learning techniques to achieve the summarization task. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of statistical learning approaches. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely sub-category as the paper deals with identifying and summarizing important information from clinical narrative texts. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper may involve the use of neural networks for the summarization task.
